lblZeekinAnalyticsProvides.default: Jydad Analytics provides digital analytics for your web site visitors with a web presence. It covers all visitors’ page navigations, engagements etc. Analytics will be displayed in terms of some dimensions and Metrics.

lblDimensionAttribute.default: A dimension is a descriptive attribute or characteristic of an object that can be given different values. For example, a geographic location could have dimensions called City Name. Values for the City Name dimension could be San Francisco, Berlin, or Singapore.

lblDimensionAnalytics.default: Dimensions which we are using in our analytics are follows

lblDimensionsAppearReports.default: Dimensions appear all of your reports, though you might see different ones depending on the specific report.

lblMetricsIndivudalDimension.default: Metrics are individual elements of a dimension that can be measured as a sum or a ratio. For example, The dimension City can be associated with a metric like Population, which would have a sum value of all the residents of the specific city. Visits, Avg. Page Visit, and Avg. Page Visit Duration are examples of metrics in Jydad Analytics.

lblMetricsAnylticsFollows.default: Metrics which we are using in our analytics are follows

lblBasicallyDashboardGraph.default:
Basically we are providing 2 types of reports, in dash board graphical representation and in detailed page listing reports.
Dash board reports contains 1 aggregative information and 7 Dimensions reports

lblLastReportsDetails.default: All of the above reports will show by default last 7 days details and it can be filterable with 90 days date range and on basis of traffic platform.

lblDetailedPageReports.default: Each detailed page reports will be available in 2 types

lblLastMonthsData.default: Last 5 months data will be available in date wise, we can generate reports within date ranges for those last 5 month's analytics data. If we wish to get reports for a period which is before 5 month it will be available in month base i.e. There will be a year selection and can be specify which months' details need to include in report.

lblMetricSessions.default: This metric is a count of sessions (visits) that have been active on our site for the selected date range. A visit is a group of interactions that take place on our website within a given time frame. For example a single visit can contain multiple page views, searches, social sharing, login, registration and product purchase etc. After 30 minutes of inactivity a visit will ends.

lblVisitorsArrives.default: When a visitor, say A, arrives on your site, Analytics starts counting from that moment. If 30 minutes pass without any kind of interaction from A, the visit ends. However, Every time A interacts with an element (like an page click), Jydad Analytics resets the expiration time by adding on an additional 30 minutes from the time of that interaction.

lblVisitorAnalyticsCookies.default: A visitor who did not have Analytics cookies when they hit the first page in this visit. If a visitor deletes their cookies and comes back to the site, the visitor will be counted as a new visitor.
A visitor with existing Analytics cookies from a previous visit. It can be calculated by deducting the new visit percentage from the total visit

lblUniqueDashoard.default: Unique visit will be only displayed on dash board Date based Visitors Overview report on date basis, because it’s not aggregative value. Unique visit is not related with the new and returning visit.

lblPageViewsDivided.default: Page views divided by visits. This metric shows the average number of pages viewed per visit.

lblTotalVisitDuration.default: Total visit duration divided by visits. This metric shows the average visit duration per visit.

lblGuestUsers.default: For the guest users take the distinct Analytics cookies and for the logged user takes the distinct user ids Then the total day’s unique visit will be sum of distinct Analytics cookies and distinct user ids.
